<body>
  <p>At the fall of Nineveh, two kingdoms were established, the Chaldean in the south, and the Medo-Persian on the eastern plateaus. Nebuchadnezzar, the Chaldean, built Babylon anew so that it surpassed Nineveh in the splendor of its palaces, temples, and Hanging Gardens. This is the Babylon of which the Greek traveler Herodotus wrote.</p>

  <h2>Explore Further:</h2>
