  <p>Fig. 137. Capital from the Palace of Artaxerxes at Susa. Height of column approximately 67 feet. This architectural element is housed in the Louvre Museum, Paris, and is a remarkable testament to the grandeur of ancient Persia's architectural achievements.</p>

