  <p>Fig. 138. Frieze of Archers. Glazed tile. From the palace of Darius at Susa. Height approximately 5 feet. This magnificent piece of glazed tile frieze is housed in the Louvre Museum, Paris, showcasing the artistry and grandeur of ancient Persia's architectural heritage.</p>

